Gold Retreats After Exceeding $1,800 for First Time on Demand for Safety

-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 
2011-08-11T02:29:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/gold-retreats-after-exceeding-1-800-for-first-time-on-demand-for-safety.html
Spot gold fell as much as 0.6
percent to $1,782.55 an ounce and last traded at $1,783.57 by
10:28 a.m. Singapore time. It earlier climbed to a record
$1,814.95 an ounce, exceeding $1,800 for the first time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
